mocDescription: This is a MOC of Ukraines Zenit 2M rocket. The two stages can be seperated. The fairing holds space for a payload.

mocDescription: This is a MOC of North Koreas Chollima-1 rocket. The three stages can be seperated. The fairing holds no space for a payload.

partsExtra: Can be build completely out of Lego bricks.

mocDescription: This is a MOC of the the VentureStar. It has a openable payload compartment. The wings are hinged and can be moved around.
rocketDescription: VentureStar was a SSTO reusable launch system developed by Lockheed Martin. It would launch vertically and land on a runway. It was powered by linear aerospike engines.

partsExtra: Can be build completely out of Lego bricks.

rocketDescription: The ELA-3 Launchtable is the transporter and launchtable for the European Ariane 5 rocket.
title: ELA-3 Launchtable
partsExtra: Can be build completely out of Lego bricks.

mocDescription: This is a MOC of the Ariane 5 ECA rocket with JWST. The fairing holds a small JWST model. The boosters as well as the upper stage of the rocket can be seperated.
rocketDescription: The Ariane 5 ECA rocket is Europes heavy orbital launch vehicle. In 2021 it launches the James Webb Space Telescope.
partsExtra: Can be build completely out of Lego bricks. You will need to cut some hoses to the correct lengths though.

mocDescription: This is a MOC of the Long March 3C/E rocket. It has two seperatable boosters and a total of three stages. All of them can be seperated from each other. The fairing holds some space for a small payload.
rocketDescription: The Long March 3C/E rocket is a chinese orbital launcher. It has 2 boosters and 3 stages. It first launched in 2014 and has launched 7 more times till then.
partsExtra: This MOC can be completely build out of Lego parts.
title: Long March 3C/E

mocDescription: This is a MOC of the Long March 3B/E rocket. It has four seperatable boosters and a total of three stages. All of them can be seperated from each other. The fairing holds some space for a small payload.
rocketDescription: The Long March 3B/E rocket is a chinese orbital launcher. It has 4 boosters and 3 stages. It first launched in 2007 and has launched more than 75 times till then.
partsExtra: This MOC can be completely build out of Lego parts.

mocDescription: This is a MOC of the Long March 3A rocket. It has a first, second and third stage which can all be seperated. The fairing holds some space for a small payload.
rocketDescription: The Long March 3A rocket is a Chinese orbital rocket. It has three stages. It first launched in 1994 and flew until 2018 with a total of 27 launches.
partsExtra: This MOC can be completely build out of Lego parts.

mocDescription: This is a MOC of the Long March 3 rocket. It has a first, second and third stage which can all be seperated. There are two fairing variants available.
rocketDescription: The Long March 3 rocket is the first rocket of the Long March 3 series of rockets. It had no boosters and three stages. It first launched in 1984 and flew until 2000 with a total of 13 launches. It was succeeded  by the Long March 3A.

rocketDescription: The Ariane 5G is a European orbital rocket system that is being launched from French Guiana. It was first launched in 1996. Since then the Ariane 5 series, which also includes the G+, ESV and ECA variants has launched 116 times with a last launch planned for 2023.
partsExtra: The MOC can be completely build out of Lego parts.

mocDescription: This is a MOC of the Vulcan Centaur 2S Peregrine rocket. The boosters can be seperated from the core stage. The Centaur second stagte can be seperated from the core stage. The payload fairings hold some space for a small payload, but not enough for the Peregrine lander. The MOC also includes a small stand for the rocket for vertical display.
rocketDescription: The Vulcan Centaur 2S is ULAs newest rocket. The first flight is planned for 2023 with Astrobotics Peregrine lunar lander as its payload. The rocket has two solid boosters on its side and a short payload fairing as well as the Centaur V upper stage.
partsExtra: The MOC can be completely build out of Lego parts.
title: Vulcan Centaur 2S Peregrine

mocDescription: This is a MOC of Astrobotics Peregrine lunar lander. It has the Iris Lunar Rover as a payload on it.
rocketDescription: Astrobotics Peregrine lunar lander is planned to launch on ULAs first Vulcan rocket and land on the moon in 2023. The Peregrine lander can carry up to 265 kg of cargo to the lunar surface. As propellant for the main engines and attitude thruster it uses MON-25/MMH.
partsExtra: The MOC can be completely build out of Lego parts.
title: Peregrine Lander

mocDescription: This is a MOC of the OK-GLI glide test vehicle for the Buran program. The payload doors can be opened (I don't know if the real one was able to though).
rocketDescription: The OK-GLI test vehicle was a Soviet plane that was used for 25 test flights between 1985 and 1988 before being retired.
partsExtra: The MOC needs a few bricks that Lego does not have in those colors, I recommend getting them from BlueBrixx or so.
title: OK-GLI

mocDescription: This is a MOC of the Buran spacecraft. The payload doors can be opened.
rocketDescription: The Buran spaceplane was a Soviet reusable spaceplane.
partsExtra: The spacecraft can be build completely out of Lego bricks.
title: Buran

mocDescription: This is a MOC of the Energia rocket with Buran as payload. The boosters and the orbiter can be seperated from the core stage. The Buran orbiter can open its paylaod bay and move its robotic arms. The orbiters tail is a bit longer than the rest of the stack, so if you want to display it it either needs a small elevated stand under the engines or needs to stand of the edge of the shelf.
rocketDescription: The Energia Buran rocket stack was a Soviet launch vehicle that could deliver a reusable spaceplane into low earth orbit. In 1985 it flew its only flight ever from pad 110/37 in Baikonur.
partsExtra: The rocket can be build completely out of Lego bricks, some hoses need to be cut for it though.
title: Energia Buran

mocDescription: This is a MOC of the Zond spacecraft.
rocketDescription: The Soyuz 7K-L1 'Zond', was a Soviet spacecraft to be used for manned lunar missions. It was launched on unmanned test flights to the moon on a Proton rocket and was eventually to be able to carry two people around the moon. It never flew any humans.
partsExtra: The spacecraft can be build completely out of Lego bricks.
title: Zond

mocDescription: This is a MOC of the Chinese Zhuque 1 rocket. The second stage can be seperated from the core stage and the third stage and the fairing can be seperated from the 2nd stage. The payload fairing holds no space for a payload.
rocketDescription: The Zhuque 1 rocket (also known as ZQ-1) is a Chinese rocket by the company LandSpace. It has three stages, all of them being solid fueled. Its only launch in 2018 resulted in a failure.
partsExtra: The rocket can be build completely out of Lego bricks, but it needs some printed parts.
title: Zhuque 1

mocDescription: This is a MOC of the Long March 4A rocket. The second stage can be seperated from the core stage and the third stage can be seperated from the 2nd stage. The payload fairing holds no space for a payload.
rocketDescription: The Long March 4A rocket (also known as LM-4A or CZ-4A) is a Chinese orbital rocket. It has three stages, with all of them being fueled by NTO/UDMH. It has a payload capacity of around 4 tons to LEO. The first of two launches happened in 1988 and the second launch in 1990.
partsExtra: The rocket can be build completely out of Lego bricks.
title: Long March 4A

mocDescription: This is a MOC of the Long March 4C rocket. The second stage can be seperated from the core stage and the third stage can be seperated from the 2nd stage. The payload fairing holds some space for a small included satellite. There are multiple fairing variants that can be build
rocketDescription: The Long March 4C rocket (also known as LM-4C or CZ-4C) is a Chinese orbital rocket. It has three stages, with all of them being fueled by NTO/UDMH. It has a payload capacity of around 4.2 tons to LEO and was first launched in 2006.
partsExtra: The rocket can be build completely out of Lego bricks.
title: Long March 4C

mocDescription: This is a MOC of the Long March 8 rocket with two boosters. The second stage and the two boosters can be seperated from the core stage. The payload fairing holds some space for a small payload.
rocketDescription: The Long March 8 rocket (also known as LM-8 or CZ-8) is a Chinese orbital rocket. It has two stages ad two boosters. The first stage and the boosters are being fueled by RP1/LOX and the second stage by LH2/LOX. It has a payload capacity of around 5 tons to SSO and first launched in 2020.
partsExtra: The rocket can be build completely out of Lego bricks.
title: Long March 8

mocDescription: This is a MOC of the Long March 8 rocket. The second stage can be seperated from the core stage. The payload fairing holds some space for a small payload.
rocketDescription: The Long March 8 rocket (also known as LM-8 or CZ-8) is a Chinese orbital rocket. It has two stages, the first being fueled by RP1/LOX and the second stage by LH2/LOX. It has a payload capacity of around 3 tons to SSO and first launched in 2022.
partsExtra: The rocket can be build completely out of Lego bricks.
title: Long March 8

mocDescription: This is a MOC of the Long March 7A rocket. The four boosters can be seperated form the core. The second stage can be seperated from the core stage and the third stage can be seperated from the second stage. The payload fairing holds some space for a small payload.
rocketDescription: The Long March 7A rocket (also known as LM-7A or CZ-7A) is a Chinese orbital rocket. It has four boosters and two stages fueled by RP-1/LOX and a third LH2/LOX fueled stage. It has a payload capacity of around 6 tons to GTO and first launched in 2020.
partsExtra: The rocket can be build completely out of Lego bricks.
title: Long March 7A

mocDescription: This is a MOC of the Long March 7 rocket. The four boosters can be seperated form the core. The second stage can be seperated from the core stage. The payload fairing holds some space for a small payload.
rocketDescription: The Long March 7 rocket (also known as LM-7 or CZ-7) is a Chinese orbital rocket. It has four boosters and two stages, all fueled by RP-1/LOX. It has a payload capacity of around 13 tons to LEO and first launched in 2016.
partsExtra: The rocket can be build completely out of Lego bricks.
title: Long March 7

mocDescription: This is a MOC of the Europa 1 rocket.
rocketDescription: The Europa 1 rocket was a European rocket that was first launched in 1968. It never reached orbit successfully. The rocket had three stages. The first stage was the british Blue streak rocket powered by two RZ-2 rocket engines. The second stage was the French Coralie stage. The third stage Astris was German.
partsExtra: The rocket can be build completely out of Lego bricks.
title: Europa 1

mocDescription: This is a MOC of the Skylon spaceplane/rocket. It has a payload bay where an upper stage and paylaod can be put in. The upper stage is an extra MOC available in the files section. The Skylon has landing gear which can be taken of. The MOC also includes a white stand as the ladning gear can't hold the MOC upright by itself.
rocketDescription: Skylon is a British concept for a reusable SSTO spaceplane by Reaction Engines Limited. It uses the SABRE propulsion engine which uses liquid hydrogen and oxygen. It could carry up to 17 tons of payload into LEO.
partsExtra: The rocket can be build completely out of Lego bricks. The upper stage has 31 parts.
title: Skylon

mocDescription: This is a MOC of the Diamant B rocket.

rocketDescription: The Tiangong Space Station is Chinas newest low earth orbit space station. It is currently made out of three modules: Tianhe, Wentian, Mengtian. Its has an operational height of 400 kilometers and three docking ports to allow different spacecraft to dock.
partsExtra: Can be build completely out of Lego bricks.
title: Tiangong Space Station

mocDescription: An Atlas V rocket can be placed on top of it (I haven't tested it so it might need a few extra bricks to hold it up). The MOC does not include the Atlas V rocket. The Train carts are not connected to the main structure.
rocketDescription: This is a MOC of the Atlas V transporter as it's being used at the Space Launch Complex 41 at the Cape Canaveral Space Force Station to launch Atlas V rockets. Before Atlas V it has launched Titan IIIC, Titan IIIE and Titan IV rockets and is planned to launch ULAs Vulcan rocket in the future. The transporter holds the rocket as it's transported from the Vertical Integration Building all the way to launch.
partsExtra: Can be build completely out of Lego bricks.
title: LC-41 Atlas V Transporter
stabilityExtra: I am really not sure how stable the whole thing actually is and if it can hold an Atlas V or if that needs some extra bricks below.

mocDescription: The Dnepr rocket is a three staged launch vehicle converted from the R-36MU ICBM. The first launch was in 1999 and the last one in 2015. It launched a total of 22 times.
partsExtra: Can be build completely out of Lego bricks.

mocDescription: The Epsilon rocket launches from the Uchinoura Space Center in Japan. The launchpad has before been used for the M series of rockets.
partsExtra: Can be build completely out of Lego bricks.
title: Epsilon Launchpad

mocDescription: The Ariane 5 ECA (Evolution Cryotechnique Type A) is the latest version of the Ariane 5 launcher. It can launch up to 10.9 tons in GTO. It first flew in 2002 and will fly it's last flight in 2023. It is known for launching the James Webb Space Telscope as well as many communication satellites.
title: Ariane 5 ECA
